  "texts": [
    "The idea is that our distilled model functions as a binary classification model, determining whether a given malicious query will elicit a toxic response from the LLM.",
    "The toxicity of LLM output is judged using the Perspective API mentioned in Section 4.1.",
    "Adhering to the API's documentation, we set the threshold value at 0.7.",
    "This implies that toxicity scores exceeding 0.7 indicate a malicious query, whereas scores below 0.7 suggest non-toxic content.",
    "Mathematically, the agreement metric is calculated as:𝐴𝑔𝑟𝑒𝑒𝑚𝑒𝑛𝑡 = Number of Consistent ClassificationsTotal Number of Queries Additionally, we employ the method outlined in Section 3.2 to compute the loss, which serves as another metric."
